---
alwaysApply: true
---

UI implemented using Flutter in the `app-flutter` directory.
Business logic and use cases live entirely in Rust; Flutter only calls the generated bridge.

Rules:

- Pages are container widgets (suffix `Pages`, e.g. `LoginPage`).
- Child widgets are presentation-only and receive data via constructor params.
- Widgets must not contain business logic.
- Pages call Rust bridge functions directly (generated by `flutter_rust_bridge` under `lib/src/rust/`).
- Use `FutureBuilder` or `StreamBuilder` to handle async bridge calls; avoid adding Dart-side state management layers unless caching across widgets is explicitly needed.
- Avoid reimplementing existing widgets; prefer Material/Cupertino components and already-defined shared widgets under `widgets/`.
- All user-facing strings must be localised via ARB files in `l10n/`, accessed through `AppLocalizations.of(context)`. This includes error messages.
- No use cases, repositories, or adapters in Dart — those belong in Rust.
